    <fr:title text="Horn clauses in the weakest precondition">Horn clauses in the weakest precondition</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Quiz</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  What's:
</html:p><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \texttt {wp}(x := x + 1, p(x, y))
]]></fr:tex>
  
    
    
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" expanded="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Solution</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>
    As a reminder for assignment we simply substitute the assignment under the postcondition, so this weakest precondition evaluates to:
  </html:p>
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    p(x, y)[x \mapsto  x + 1] \equiv  p(x + 1, y)
  ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
  
